originalText.text: I absolutely love taking class with Stacy W. She is a supportive, thoughtful and inspiring teacher. She gives clear directions throughout the class, offers encouragement and really motivates every student to show up for themselves. If you are new to Solidcore (and maybe a little nervous like I was) I highly recommend her class!

originalText.text: This studio starts classes at 5:30am-6am and disturbs our morning and evening peace everyday monday through sunday. Please do not sign up for classes here as we've repeatedly asked building management and solidcore to turn down music and PA system and they refuse. Also when you drop weights on the floor it sounds like thunder!!

originalText.text:
If you are planning on going once or twice a week then solidcore is ok (personally I think BodyRok is better), but anything more than that is not worth it. I had an unlimited membership for a month and the workouts are the same every day. There's no variation.

Their customer service is also terrible. I had to ask 3 times in person to cancel my membership (the app says you MUST do it in person), then ended up having to email and call headquarters and STILL got charged an additional month.

They also randomly charged me for waters and I had to email them to remove the charges.

originalText.text: Love Solidcore! Although it can feel fast paced and challenging, the instructors are helpful and supportive. I’ve taken classes from several different coaches here and at other locations - all of whom are excellent.
